thread.title_full: College football: How the top 25 fared

author: Associated Press
title: College football: How the top 25 fared
text:
College football: How the top 25 fared Associated Press Posted: 10/24/2015 08:47:50 PM PDT Updated: 10/24/2015 10:18:19 PM PDT HOW THE AP TOP 25 FARED No. 1 Ohio State (8-0) beat Rutgers 49-7. Next: vs. Minnesota, Nov. 7. 
No. 2 Baylor (7-0) beat Iowa State 45-27. Next: at Kansas State, Nov. 5. 
No. 3 Utah (6-1) lost to USC 42-24. Next: vs. Oregon State, Saturday. 
No. 4 TCU (7-0) did not play. Next: vs. West Virginia, Thursday. 
No. 5 LSU (7-0) beat Western Kentucky 48-20. Next: at No. 8 Alabama, Nov. 7. 
No. 6 Clemson (7-0) beat Miami 58-0. Next: at N.C. State, Saturday. 
No. 7 Michigan State (8-0) beat Indiana 52-26. Next: at Nebraska, Nov. 7. 
No. 8 Alabama (7-1) beat Tennessee 19-14. Next vs. No. 5 LSU, Nov. 7. 
No. 9 Florida State (6-1) lost to Georgia Tech 22-16. Next: vs. Syracuse, Saturday. 
No. 10 Stanford (5-1) vs. Washington, late. Next: at Washington State, Saturday. 
No. 11 Notre Dame (6-1) did not play. Next: at No. 22 Temple, Saturday. 
No. 12 Iowa (7-0) did not play. Next: vs. Maryland, Saturday. 
No. 13 Florida (6-1) did not play. Next: vs. Georgia at Jacksonville, Florida, Saturday. 
No. 14 Oklahoma State (7-0) beat Kansas 58-10. Next: at Texas Tech, Saturday. 
No. 15 Michigan (5-2) did not play. Next: at Minnesota, Saturday. 
No. 15 Texas A&M (5-2) lost to No. 24 Mississippi 23-3. Next: vs. South Carolina, Saturday. 
No. 17 Oklahoma (6-1) beat Texas Tech 63-27. Next: at Kansas, Saturday. 
No. 18 Memphis (7-0) beat Tulsa 66-42, Friday. Next: vs. Tulane, Saturday. Advertisement 
No. 19 Toledo (7-0) beat UMass 51-35. Next: vs. Northern Illinois, Nov. 3. 
No. 20 Cal (5-2) lost to UCLA 40-24, Thursday. Next: vs. USC, Saturday. 
No. 21 Houston (7-0) beat UCF 59-10. Next: vs. Vanderbilt, Saturday. 
No. 22 Temple (7-0) beat East Carolina 24-14, Thursday. Next: vs. No. 11 Notre Dame, Saturday. 
No. 23 Duke (6-1) beat Virginia Tech 45-43, 4OT. Next: vs. Miami, Saturday. 
No. 24 Mississippi (6-2) beat No. 15 Texas A&M 23-3. Next: at Auburn, Saturday. 
No. 25 Pittsburgh (6-1) beat Syracuse 23-20. Next: vs. North Carolina, Thursday.
